name: 2010 Mustang (Shelby Cobra GT500 Plus) Sleeper
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post For Sale By Owner: 2010 Mustang (Shelby Cobra GT500 Plus) Sleeper...Wolf in Sheep's Clothing Vehicle was a 2010 V6 Coupe that was stolen and recovered but by the time it was recovered the insurance company had paid off the owner. When it was recovered the only thing wrong was that the wheels and tires were missing and yet the insurance company sent it to insurance auction which means the State Of Michigan classifies it as a "rebuilt" title. I believe this is not what should happen to a stolen and recovered vehicle with wheels and tires missing but when it comes to Michigan Secretary of State, "you can't fight city hall" (and win) as they say. The 2007 GT500 parts came from 1ZVHT88S175285929. I have documented proof for both vehicles. Purchaser of vehicle at insurance auction then stripped the body down to just the body and rotisserie painted it from V6 White to GT500 Red. It was re-assembled using 2007 GT500 Chassis, Powertrain, and Interior OEM factory pieces. It was subsequently upgraded to 2013/2014 GT500 Supercharger and tuned by Paul Svinicki at Paul's High Performance in Jackson, Michigan. The vehicle now makes 700+ hp at the engine and 600+ hp at the tires with dyno sheet proof. The vehicle is really good but is not perfect or a car show winner by aesthetics.  Asking $35,900.00 or best in person cash offer. FiveEight6 Eight2Three 35Hundred Unfortunately, I recently had a perspective buyer of a showroom new vintage moped crash it on a test ride and then said he didn't want to buy it because it was now crashed. Lesson learned: I will not let this happen again.  No test drives unless agreed upon selling price, proof of funds, and a deposit. Also, no test drives for those who are not manual transmission operation literate. Please learn on someone else's clutch.

name: 2017 Chevrolet Volt LT Hatchback 4D
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post 2017 Chevrolet Volt LT Hatchback 4D. Own an EV and not have to worry about range (range anxiety is real) as this one runs on electricity and gas. I am the only owner of this vehicle (I leased it in 2016, bought it in 2019). 82,862 total miles. But 81,282 of those miles are electric (see OnStar app pic), so only 1,580 engine miles, meaning used the onboard 4-cylinder engine (I’m OCD about driving in electric mode. When temps get below 15oF, the engine kicks on no matter what to keep the batteries conditioned and that’s where most of those ‘miles’ are from). 107 lifetime MPGe (mile per gallon equivalent), 250+ lifetime MPG. Both numbers are tops for this climate.  This car has been garage-kept (parking deck at work), VERY well taken care of, non-smoking family and driven 98+% in electric mode. The Chevy Volt is an extended-range EV where an engine kicks in to charge the battery if you run out of charge. Full-charge range is around 70 miles in the summer (see recent pic) and 50 in the winter on the coldest of days (around 0oF). A full tank of gas will take this car another 400 miles after the battery charge is used up (10 gallon tank and 40+ miles per gallon).  Thermal imaging pics prove heating/cooling and steering wheel heating all work just fine. Bluetooth Wireless connection for hands-free communication, AM/FM Radio w/MyLink, Backup Camera, F&R Side Air Bags, Dual Air Bags, Knee Air Bags, F&R Head Curtain Air Bags, Traction Control, StabiliTrak, ABS (4-Wheel), Tilt & Telescoping Wheel, Keyless Start (can also start the car through the OnStar app which is great for having a warm car to get into in the winter before leaving from work or home). Paid off, no accidents, no issues, no dash lights, clean title. Pulled CarFax report on 8/16/23. Both key fobs work. New front tires Nov 2022. Voltec warranty good to 8 years and 100,000 miles and 8 years is up NEXT September (2024). Great car, just don’t need it any more (have 4 kids taking classes at the college that I teach at so won’t need my own vehicle for years to come). Comparable: Carvana #1: https://www.carvana.com/vehicle/2799448 Carvana #2: https://www.carvana.com/vehicle/2768381 Carvana #3: https://www.carvana.com/vehicle/2799118 Some of these comps have slightly less total miles, but not less engine miles. Only 1,580 engine miles on my car and that engine is going to last a very long time.

seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post Wolfsburg Edition in Montego Black Metallic  140k~ Miles on Body  1k~ Miles on engine  The car is in great shape, is fun to drive, and shifts and runs flawlessly. It could use a few finishing touches or drive it as is. I purchased the car about 5 years ago, but due to some oil pressure issues, the engine was replaced approximately 3 years ago (Approximately 1200 miles since installation). The engine was brand new from Germany still wrapped in plastic. It is a 1.8L (MK3 block) with upgraded JH hydraulic head originally intended for the VW factory in Mexico. The person I bought the engine from purchased a large batch of engines from VW as the factory had shut down before the engines were ever installed. During the installation, I replaced essentially everything along the way. The only "performance" upgrade I did was a lower from stress bar to tighten up the stock suspension setup. The Montego black Wolfsburg option included body-colored wheel arches, bumpers, and mirror caps from the factory. The wheel arches would use some rattle can work to make them perfect again.  New parts (within the last 3 years):  Engine (complete)  Clutch kit  Injectors and cups  Axles  Tie Rods  Front brakes  Rear shocks  Radiator  Waterpump  Thermostat  Radiator hoses  Engine Mounts  Euro Sport 4-point Lower Front Stress Bar  Many other bits including sensors, gaskets, relays, etc.  Known Problems:  Front windshield seal needs replacement (New parts included)  Slow battery drain from radio circuit (Can demonstrate by removing fuse or disconnecting radio)  HVAC fan doesn’t work  Slight oil pan drip (2-3 drops) when parked if the car gets nice and hot after a drive  Speedo indicates exactly 10 mph over actual speed  I never fixed any of the problems because I used the car purely in the summer on nice days. It didn’t seem necessary when I keep it on a 12v tender and don’t drive in the rain.  I’m happy top answer any questions.  Keywords: Cabriolet, Cabrio, GTI, Volkswagen, Wolfsburg, Mk1

I can imagin...
seller_notes: QR Code Link to This Post -1984 Chevy Camaro Z28 5.0 H.O. L69 -Original 49K Miles -Light Blue Metallic Exterior -Blue Interior -5 Speed Manual, RWD -Org. ERS sound system -Org. Craftsman “Shadow” Rear Spoiler I received this sentimental 49k mile vehicle from the original owner Retired US Army family (He had passed).  My objective, to help get it back on the road as we worked in the same industry.  This amazing Camaro was garage kept its whole life looks to not have been driven in the winter months.  I can imagine how happy the original owner was when he bought this Z28 new, only 2 years after he joined the US Army, sole owner from July 1984 - Jan2023 (At that time I took possession).   The vehicle includes all records; original Ziebart receipt when purchasing the car, all Registration and Insurance slips indicating single ownership, dealership mile certification, and manuals. About the car.  This good condition 1984 Chevrolet Camaro Z28 with the optional High Output Package 5-liter V8 blue on blue is a beautiful time capsule of a single owner Metro Detroit Retired US Army service member who was part of a Camaro club that met at events around Detroit over the years.  One could imagine him driving this Z28 5spd to the Detroit Tank Arsenal in the summer months as happy as anyone could be. I respectfully restored this car to “road worthy status” keeping the car as original as I possibly could upon receipt.  To include the original self-made tape/stereo he had in the car at the time it was parked in 1997.  Here is a list of what I mean by road worthy status…Pictures are available of each step if interested.   My definition of Road Worthy Status::: With a car, this age, there are a few rubber parts that will become brittle and original leaded fuel that gums up over time as it evaporates when a vehicle sits.  Those items are what I focused on.  Please see the list below.  Note: all receipts available upon request. New; rear shocks, front struts, front/rear torsion bar bushings, front rotors/rear drum/brakes/calipers/cylinder, master brake cylinder/brake booster, front inner/outer wheel bearings and seals, front/rear brake lines, dual rear emergency brake cables, front/rear BF Goodrich P245/60R15 100S M+S Radial T/A tires, fluids [rear dif/axle, oil/filter, power steering, gear box, radiator], rear fuel tank/straps/fuel pump kit, flushed fuel lines, OEM carburetor seals/throttle body sensor/clean jets/secondaries, upper/lower radiator hoses, electric cooling fan, all belts, windshield wipers, thermostat, radiator cap, air filter, spark plugs/cap/rotor, professional 2 stage paint buff/wax/interior/engine detailed, front/rear hood/trunk gas struts, interior exterior light bulbs where needed, battery, and Cherry Bomb exhaust. The car is 40 years old next year so the paint does have a few surface things that are expected in a Midwest vehicle. But nothing that a professional could not touch up if someone wanted to make it perfect, I purposely left alone as it is how I received it. There were some small paint repairs done many years ago and a few surface rust spots that were a result from the OEM hood protector that collected water.  But the original Ziebart did a wonderful job of preserving the Z28 for its 39 years of service.   The Z28, I believe, with the low mileage and few paint areas is priced well, all work done to the car is priced fair. With that said, I am willing to negotiate. For those that want a solid base vehicle with a plan to drop in a loping crate engine making it a sexy sleeper, well this is a perfect car to have fun with…..  Or if you simply want to start driving today, do a few burn outs at a light in a no check engine light ready to drive 1984 Z28 5 speed that gets thumbs up wherever you go then leave it as is…….a time capsule with all its records intact!   The Camaro Z28 is a special performance automobile in its day.  This particular year Z28 won motor trends car of the year awards for handling/performance. If preserved in this good condition, it's a truly rare and noteworthy all records daily driver find. I am Wishing the next owner will be the steward of the original owner’s story, his service to our country, and overall proud to drive a true piece of automotive history. Please call/text with name and number to arrange an appointment, feel free to get in touch anytime call/text if you have questions.
